      ],
      "content": "Weathered planks creak beneath your feet as the dock juts out over grey-green water. Fishing boats knock gently against their moorings, their paint flaking in long pale strips. The smell of salt and tar hangs in the still air.\n\nGulls cry overhead, and ropes creak against the pilings.\n\nA cobbled road leads **north** toward the village, and a sandy path follows the shoreline **east**."
    },
    {
      "kind": 30078,
      "tags": [
