          "sound",
          "30078:<PUBKEY>:tides-end-08-sound:sound:tavern-fire",
          "ambient",
          "0.6"
        ]
      ],
      "content": "The low-ceilinged room is warm and dim, lit by tallow candles guttering in glass jars. A long bar of driftwood planks runs along the far wall, its surface stained dark with years of spilled ale. A fire crackles in a stone hearth, and the murmur of conversation drifts from somewhere unseen.\n\nThe only way out is **west**, back to the square."
    },
